# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [V0.9.2] - 2026-05-24
### Changed
- Bugfix (Physics Engine): Resolved a known issue where "True Complex Field" mode produced slightly asymmetrical 3D spatial volumes even with perfectly symmetrical speaker placement.
- Math Model Update: Modified the phase interference mathematical approximation in `get_psi`. Shifted the reference point of the phase delay (imaginary component) from the origin ($0$) to the center of the room ($L/2$). This ensures perfectly symmetric boundary reflection conditions for opposing walls.

## [V0.9.1] - 2026-05-24
### Changed
- Refactoring: Separated paramaters into an independent module (`config.py`).
- Refactoring: Separated core physics calculation logic into an independent module (`physics.py`).
- Refactoring: Extracted Plotly 2D/3D rendering logic into a dedicated module (`render.py`).
- Refactoring: Streamlined `main.py` to act purely as a UI controller and data flow manager, adopting an MVC-like architecture.
- Optimization: Removed redundant `SimConfig` dataclass and integrated global parameter references directly via `config.py`.
- Architecture: Established a modular foundation to facilitate future standalone desktop application development.

## [V0.9.0] - 2026-05-23

### Added
- Redesigned 2D Top-Down View (Mode 1): Replaced the 3D wireframe in the placement mode with a flat, responsive 2D scatter plot (XY plane) to improve UX. Z-axis data is preserved as text labels.
- Precise Measurement Rulers: Implemented an edge-to-edge ruler system in Mode 1 with major ticks at 0.5m intervals and inward minor ticks at 0.1m intervals. Visual aspect ratio is strictly locked to 1:1.
- 1/4 Subdivision Grid: Introduced a 4x4 internal grid into both the 3D wireframe (Mode 2) and 2D view (Mode 1) to easily identify 1/2 and 1/4 wavelength nodes/antinodes.
- Room Modes Analytics Table (Mode 3): Added a data table calculating equivalent length and resonant frequencies (1st to 3rd order) for the 7 fundamental room modes. Included a one-click CSV export function (UTF-8 with BOM).

### Changed
- Statistical Volume Scaling (+/- 2 sigma): Overhauled 3D volumetric color mapping to use a robust +/- 2 sigma range (covering ~95.4% of the data), preventing the visuals from being washed out by extreme local outliers.
- Refined Volume Visuals: Adjusted volumetric thresholds to map the top 30% to peaks and bottom 30% to valleys. Reduced opacity to 0.25 and increased surface count to 8 for a smoother "cloud-like" visual.
- Codebase Cleanup: Removed legacy/redundant comments and replaced Japanese comments with concise English documentation to improve future maintainability.

## [V0.8.2] - 2026-05-22

### Changed
- **Dual-Trace Volumetric Rendering**: Split the 3D standing wave visualization into two distinct volume traces to simultaneously render "Valleys" (nodes) and "Peaks" (anti-nodes).
- **Optimized Visibility Thresholds**: Adjusted rendering percentiles to explicitly show the 2%–25% range (deep valleys) and 75%–98% range (high peaks). The middle 50% of the pressure field is now rendered transparently, drastically reducing visual occlusion and making the internal room structure much easier to interpret.
- **Color Scale & Minimum Normalization**: Updated `global_min` to use the 2nd percentile (`np.percentile(tensor_abs, 2)`) instead of the absolute mathematical minimum. This prevents the color scale and volume bounds from being heavily skewed by extreme singularity points (perfect phase cancellations).

##　[V0.8.1] - 2026-05-21
### Added
- Spatial Smoothing Feature: Introduced a toggle switch in "1. Layout Placement" mode to enable 3x3x3 spatial smoothing (±10cm offsets, 27 points) around the microphone position. This simulates real-world acoustic measurements by averaging out extreme local dips and providing a more perceptually accurate frequency response.

- Vectorized Core Processing: Implemented advanced NumPy vectorization in compute_f_response_1d to calculate multiple microphone positions simultaneously, ensuring that the 27-point spatial smoothing maintains ultra-fast performance without noticeable lag.

### Refactored
- Code Standardization & Documentation: Completely overhauled the codebase documentation. Removed outdated/cluttered development comments and introduced professional, standard English docstrings for all classes and functions.

- Architectural Cleanup: Grouped code into logical blocks (Data Models, Application State, UI Setup, Core Physics Engine, Rendering) with clear structural comments, greatly enhancing code readability and maintainability for future expansions (e.g., desktop/near-field acoustic models).

## [V0.7.3] - 2026-05-20

### Added
- "High Resolution Mode" toggle in the sidebar to enable 32x32x32 grid and 2Hz steps for high-spec machines.
- "Large 3D View" toggle in the sidebar to dynamically increase the 3D plot height up to 800px.
- "Pause" button next to the "Play" button in the 3D viewer to immediately interrupt the frequency sweep animation and prevent browser freezing.

### Changed
- Reduced the default 3D volume rendering grid size to 24x24x24 with 5Hz steps to lower memory consumption and improve performance on laptops.
- Decreased the default 3D plot height from 700px to 500px to ensure the 3D canvas and frequency slider fit perfectly within standard laptop screens (e.g., 1080p) without vertical scrolling.

## [V0.7.2] - 2026-05-19
### Added
- **Default State Externalization**: Extracted all hardcoded initial UI values into a single `DEFAULT_STATE` dictionary, paving the way for future JSON save/load functionality.
- **Dynamic L/R Symmetry Link**: Introduced a toggle switch for stereo mode to automatically mirror Speaker 2's position based on Speaker 1.
- **Smart UI Space Management**: Dynamically hides Speaker 2's sliders when the symmetry link is active to save vertical sidebar space and prevent state conflicts.
- **State Persistence on Unlink**: Implemented a session state logic that seamlessly preserves Speaker 2's calculated position when the symmetry link is toggled off, allowing the user to resume manual adjustments from that exact point.
- **Dynamic Slider Bounds**: Added a safety constraint that automatically limits Speaker 1's maximum X-axis value to half of the room width (`Lx / 2.0`) when the symmetry link is active, preventing Speaker 2 from exceeding the room dimensions.

### Changed
- **Increased Room Dimension Precision**: Lowered the minimum room dimensions (Lx, Ly, Lz) to 1.0m and increased slider precision to 0.02m steps for finer adjustments.

## [V0.7.1] - 2026-05-18
### Refactored
- **Introduced Dataclasses**: Implemented `@dataclass` for `RoomConfig`, `Position`, and `SimConfig` to structure application state and configuration parameters.
- **Improved Function Signatures**: Updated core physics functions (`compute_f_response_1d` and `compute_tensor_3d`) to accept dataclass objects instead of multiple primitive variables, drastically improving readability.
- **Safe Unpacking Mechanism**: Utilized internal variable unpacking within calculation functions to preserve the integrity of the complex physical simulation logic without rewriting the core math.
- **Helper Function Modularization**: Updated physics helper functions (`get_max_modes`, `calc_gamma`) to accept `RoomConfig` and `SimConfig`, laying the groundwork for a standalone `PhysicsEngine` module.
- **UI and Logic Separation**: Fully decoupled the rendering section from raw UI sidebar variables by mapping drawing functions (e.g., `draw_room_wireframe`) to the newly created dataclass properties (`room.Lx`, `eff_room.Lx`, etc.).

## [V0.7.0] - 2026-05-18
### Added
- Stereo mode (two sound source)
- Calcuration mode selection in the stereo mode. True complex field calcuration mode is experimental.

## [V0.2.0] - 2026-05-17
### Added
- High-precision (1cm) slider steps for accurate equipment placement.
- Improved frequency resolution in 1D mode to 1Hz steps (20Hz-200Hz).
- Improved frequency resolution in 3D mode to 2Hz steps (20Hz-200Hz).

### Changed
- Fixed 3D visualization grid resolution to 32x32x32 to maintain consistent performance regardless of room size.
- Changed Volume Rendering surface_count from 15 to 12 for performance optimization.

## [V0.1.0] - 2026-05-16
### Added
- Initial release of the Standing Wave Viewer.
- 3D Volume rendering of room standing waves.
- UI controls for room dimensions, equipment placement, and wall reflection coefficients.